YOLA – A member of the National Assembly RT. Hon Dr. Mustapha Saidu has called all Nígerians to join the Peoples Democratic Party PDP because, according to him, the party would take over the country in 2023. Speaking immediately after the former minister of health Dr. Idi Hong, formerly joined the PDP in Adamawa State. Dr. Mustapha Saidu who represents Song -Fufore federal constituency in the National Assembly said by so doing Nigerians of goodwill will contribute to bringing the party to power. He said he was confident that PDP will also retain power in Adamawa State in 2023 because of the laudable projects executed by Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri in the first four years. He pointed out that only PDP can guarantee security which has now completely broken irreparably as more souls are been lost to armed Bandits all over the nation. Dr. Mustapha pointed out that the PDP can rescue Nigeria as things stand now because the country is facing serious problems but the PDP will put smiles on the faces of Nigerians in 2023. Also speaking Dr. Idi Hong the former minister of health said he had joined the PDP because there is no other party that can handle the country but PDP because of his experience in handling security matters.Dr. Idi Hong said Nígerians should join the PDP such that it would be easy for the party to take over Government Houses across the country. 21 LGAs chairmen who recently got elected in the just concluded Local Government elections.